ZH: 在某些国家，死刑是合法的。
EN: In some countries, the death penalty is legal.

ZH: 犯罪分子可能会面临死刑的惩罚。
EN: Criminals may face the punishment of the death penalty.

ZH: 他因犯下重罪被判处死刑。
EN: He was sentenced to death for committing a serious crime.

ZH: 死刑是有争议的处罚方式。
EN: The death penalty is a controversial form of punishment.

ZH: 许多人认为死刑是一种残酷的惩罚。
EN: Many people believe that the death penalty is a cruel punishment.

ZH: 没有足够的证据来支持死刑的使用。
EN: There is not enough evidence to support the use of the death penalty.

ZH: 法官对死刑的态度是严格的。
EN: Judges have a strict attitude towards the death penalty.

ZH: 死刑在一些国家被视为有效的犯罪防治措施。
EN: The death penalty is seen as an effective crime deterrent in some countries.

ZH: 死刑执行的方式各国有所不同。
EN: The methods of carrying out the death penalty vary from country to country.

ZH: 很多人支持废除死刑。
EN: Many people support the abolition of the death penalty.

ZH: 在一些地方，死刑被用于惩罚政治犯。
EN: In some places, the death penalty is used to punish political prisoners.

ZH: 死刑在一些宗教中被认可。
EN: The death penalty is recognized in some religions.

ZH: 有些律师专门为死刑犯辩护。
EN: Some lawyers specialize in defending death row inmates.

ZH: 他们为废除死刑而努力奋斗。
EN: They are fighting for the abolition of the death penalty.

ZH: 死刑的执行会引发国际社会的关注。
EN: The execution of the death penalty attracts international attention.

ZH: 年轻人对死刑的态度可能会有所不同。
EN: The attitudes of young people towards the death penalty may vary.

ZH: 死刑的存在引发了辩论和争议。
EN: The existence of the death penalty has sparked debate and controversy.

ZH: 对死刑的态度取决于个人的价值观和信仰。
EN: Attitudes towards the death penalty depend on individual values and beliefs.

ZH: 一些人认为死刑是对犯罪行为的必要回应。
EN: Some people believe that the death penalty is a necessary response to criminal behavior.

ZH: 在某些情况下，死刑可能会被视为最后的手段。
EN: In some cases, the death penalty may be seen as a last resort.
